						               													<description>Two scoops or three? Create a sundae for each customer. The player who attracts the most customers wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Sundae, players create combinations with dominoes. The better combinations are fancier sundaes to win over customers. Attract more customers than your opponent to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To play, seven customer tokens are placed between the players, and a double nine set of dominoes (without the double blank) is shuffled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns playing a domino to their side of the row of customers and refilling their hand. Three dominoes (three scoops) make a sundae, and these sundaes are compared to see which the customer prefers. The player who claims four of the seven customers will win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sundae may also be played with two scoops (two dominoes per combination) and five customers. The player who claims three of the customers wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
